  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Bike Mechanic",
  "description": "<p><strong>Get Paid to Ride &amp; Fix (Indoor Role)</strong></p>\n<p>Love working with your hands and keeping things running smoothly? We’re looking for detail-oriented individuals to join our team as <strong>Full-Time Bike Maintenance Crew</strong>. Based in our warehouse, you’ll help ensure our fleet of shared bikes stays safe, functional, and ready to hit the streets—keeping the city moving, one repair at a time.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform routine bike repairs (brakes, tires, chains, etc.) in a workshop setting</li>\n  <li>Conduct safety checks and quality inspections on incoming and outgoing bikes</li>\n  <li>Replace damaged parts and ensure bikes meet operational standards</li>\n  <li>Record repair tasks and inventory usage using a mobile app or form</li>\n  <li>Assist with loading/unloading bikes and support warehouse operations as needed</li>\n  <li>Manage inventory and spare parts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Basic knowledge of bicycle mechanics and tools</li>\n  <li>Comfortable working in an indoor warehouse environment</li>\n  <li>Responsible, detail-oriented, and hands-on</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and collaboratively with a team</li>\n  <li>Previous experience in bike repair or mechanical work is a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why Join Us?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Get paid a basic salary of <strong>$2,500 + $300 KPI incentive</strong> to fix bikes in a comfortable indoor workspace</li>\n  <li>Enjoy hands-on work that’s both active and rewarding</li>\n  <li>Be part of a team contributing to a greener, more sustainable city</li>\n</ul>",
